e   Bagge   1) or from Middle English <i>badger</i> ‘hawker, huckster’, though this word is not recorded before 1467–8 and it is of doubtful origin. It is unlikely that the surname has anything to do with the animal (see   Brock   2), which was not known by this name until the 16th century."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Bagge was born in 1560, in Somerset, England, United Kingdom as the son of Thomas Bagge. He married Botilla Von Zijlen in 1580, in Somerset, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in November 1623, at the age of 63, and was buried in Bridport, Dorset, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1560–November 1623":"1560–november 1623","1560–1623":"1560–1623","1561–1586":"1561–1586","1581–1657":"1581–1657","1584–1624":"1584–1624","–Male":"Surnud","1624":"1624","1657":"1657","November 1623":"november 1623","1623":"1623","1586":"1586","1584":"1584","1561":"1561","1560":"1560","1581":"1581","1580":"1580","about 1581":"umbes 1581","23 Nov 1623":"23. november 1623","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Somerset,England":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom",", , England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bridport, Dorset, England":"Bridport, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chard, Somerset, England":"Chard, Somerset, England","Chardstock, Dorset, , England":"Chardstock, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1560–November 1623":"1560–marraskuu 1623","1560–1623":"1560–1623",